400 g Turkey Breast Steak
¼ cup Basil Pesto
227 g Quick-Cook Penne
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Baby Spinach
2 unit(s) Cream Cheese
237 mL Cream
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Lemon
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F. Wash and dry all produce.
Juice half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels. Season with half of the Zesty Garlic Blend and pepper. (NOTE: If turkey steaks are thicker then 1-inch, place each piece on a cutting board and cover with plastic wrap. Using a rolling pin or heavy-bottomed pan, pound each turkey steak until 1-inch thick.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey. (NOTE: Don't crowd the pan; cook in 2 batches if needed.) Pan-fry for 1-2 min, flipping half way through, until golden. Transfer turkey to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Carefully wipe the pan clean.
In a medium bowl, add pesto, half the Parmesan, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lemon juice and breadcrumbs. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine.
Spread pesto-mixture evenly over top of turkey and roast in the middle of the oven for 10-12 min, until cooked through.**

Heat the same pan over medium-high. When hot, a dd 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, cream, remaining Zesty Garlic Blend, cream cheese and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently, until cream cheese is melted.
Add penne. Reduce heat to medium. Cook for 2-4 min, stirring occasionally, until penne is tender and coated.

Meanwhile, halve baby tomatoes.
To the pan with penne, add tomatoes and spinach. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring often, until spinach wilts and sauce is slightly thickened. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between plates.
Divide turkey over top of pasta.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if you like.